```java
    static DispatchBinding current(GenerationRegistry registry) {
        GenerationLease activeLease = registry.active();
        DispatchBinding binding = ACTIVE.get();
        if (binding == null) {
            DispatchBinding created = new DispatchBinding(activeLease);
            ACTIVE.set(created);
            return created;
        }

        if (!binding.matches(activeLease)) {
            DispatchBinding replacement = new DispatchBinding(activeLease);
            ACTIVE.set(replacement);
            return replacement;
        }

        return binding;
    }
```
When `binding.matches(activeLease)` is false, a new `DispatchBinding` is created and set in the `ThreadLocal`. However, the *old* `binding` is never closed! `DispatchBinding` likely holds a reference to a `GenerationLease`. If it's not closed, the lease's reference count won't decrement, the generation won't be closed, and the ClassLoader won't be collected. This leads to Metaspace exhaustion.

